d:61:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --engine tavily\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:63:# Domain filtering (only search specific sites)\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:64:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --include-domains \\\"github.com,stackoverflow.com\\\"\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:67:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --exclude-domains \\\"pinterest.com,quora.com\\\"\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:70:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --from 2026-01-01 --to 2026-02-09\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:73:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --time-range week\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:75:# Deep/advanced search\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:76:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --deep\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:78:# News search\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:79:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --news --days 7\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:81:# Multi-engine: Baidu search\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:82:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --engine serpapi --search-engine baidu\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:85:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" -n 10\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:88:node {baseDir}/scripts/search.mjs \\\"query\\\" --json\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:108:| `--deep` | Deep/advanced search mode | tavily, exa |\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:109:| `--news` | News search mode | tavily, serper, serpapi |\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:111:| `--include-domains <d,...>` | Only search these domains | all (native: tavily, exa) |\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:116:| `--search-engine <name>` | SerpAPI sub-engine: google\\\\|bing\\\\|baidu\\\\|yandex\\\\|duckduckgo | serpapi |\\n/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/web-search-pro/SKILL.md:141:- `--search-engine <name>` always uses SerpAPI and requires `SERPAPI_API_KEY`\\n/app/skills/apple-notes/SKILL.md:3:description: Manage Apple Notes via the `memo` CLI on macOS (create, view, edit, delete, search, move, and export notes). Use when a user asks OpenClaw to add a note, list notes, search notes, or manage note folders.\\n/app/skills/apple-notes/SKILL.md:28:Use `memo notes` to manage Apple Notes directly from the terminal. Create, view, edit, delete, search, move notes between folders, and export to HTML/Markdown.\\n/app/skills/apple-notes/SKILL.md:40:- Search notes (fuzzy): `memo notes -s \\\"query\\\"`\\n/app/skills/bear-notes/SKILL.md:3:description: Create, search, and manage Bear notes via grizzly CLI.\\n/app/skills/bear-notes/SKILL.md:69:Search notes (via open-tag)\\n/app/skills/blucli/SKILL.md:45:- TuneIn search/play: `blu tunein search \\\"query\\\"`, `blu tunein play \\\"query\\\"`\\n/app/skills/bluebubbles/SKILL.md:121:- Requires gateway config `channels.bluebubbles` (serverUrl/password/webhookPath).\\n/app/skills/canvas/SKILL.md:7:The canvas tool lets you present web content on any connected node's canvas view. Great for:\\n/app/skills/canvas/SKILL.md:27:3. **Node Apps**: Render the content in a WebView\\n/app/skills/canvas/SKILL.md:81:- Injects a WebSocket client into HTML files\\n/app/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md:3:description: Use the ClawHub CLI to search, install, update, and publish agent skills from clawhub.com. Use when you need to fetch new skills on the fly, sync installed skills to latest or a specific version, or publish new/updated skill folders with the npm-installed clawhub CLI.\\n/app/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md:38:Search\\n/app/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md:41:clawhub search \\\"postgres backups\\\"\\n/app/skills/discord/SKILL.md:168:Search:\\n/app/skills/discord/SKILL.md:172:  \\\"action\\\": \\\"search\\\",\\n/app/skills/gh-issues/SKILL.md:391:- Search the codebase (grep/find) for the relevant code. Can you locate it?\\n/app/skills/gh-issues/SKILL.md:405:3. ANALYZE — Search the codebase to find relevant files:\\n/app/skills/gifgrep/SKILL.md:3:description: Search GIF providers with CLI/TUI, download results, and extract stills/sheets.\\n/app/skills/gifgrep/SKILL.md:34:Use `gifgrep` to search GIF providers (Tenor/Giphy), browse in a TUI, download results, and extract stills or sheets.\\n/app/skills/gifgrep/SKILL.md:38:- Search → preview → download → extract (still/sheet) for fast review and sharing.\\n/app/skills/gifgrep/SKILL.md:44:- `gifgrep search --json cats | jq '.[0].url'`\\n/app/skills/github/SKILL.md:3:description: \\\"GitHub operations via `gh` CLI: issues, PRs, CI runs, code review, API queries. Use when: (1) checking PR status or CI, (2) creating/commenting on issues, (3) listing/filtering PRs or issues, (4) viewing run logs. NOT for: complex web UI interactions requiring manual browser flows (use browser tooling when available), bulk operations across many repos (script with gh api), or when gh auth is not configured.\\\"\\n/app/skills/gog/SKILL.md:37:- Gmail search: `gog gmail search 'newer_than:7d' --max 10`\\n/app/skills/gog/SKILL.md:38:- Gmail messages search (per email, ignores threading): `gog gmail messages search \\\"in:inbox from:ryanair.com\\\" --max 20 --account you@example.com`\\n/app/skills/gog/SKILL.md:51:- Drive search: `gog drive search \\\"query\\\" --max 10`\\n/app/skills/gog/SKILL.md:116:- `gog gmail search` returns one row per thread; use `gog gmail messages search` when you need every individual email returned separately.\\n/app/skills/goplaces/SKILL.md:3:description: Query Google Places API (New) via the goplaces CLI for text search, place details, resolve, and reviews. Use for human-friendly place lookup or JSON output for scripts.\\n/app/skills/goplaces/SKILL.md:41:- Search: `goplaces search \\\"coffee\\\" --open-now --min-rating 4 --limit 5`\\n/app/skills/goplaces/SKILL.md:42:- Bias: `goplaces search \\\"pizza\\\" --lat 40.8 --lng -73.9 --radius-m 3000`\\n/app/skills/goplaces/SKILL.md:43:- Pagination: `goplaces search \\\"pizza\\\" --page-token \\\"NEXT_PAGE_TOKEN\\\"`\\n/app/skills/goplaces/SKILL.md:46:- JSON: `goplaces search \\\"sushi\\\" --json`\\n/app/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md:90:If browser control is enabled, recommend that 2FA be enabled on all important accounts, with hardware keys preferred and SMS not sufficient.\\n/app/skills/himalaya/SKILL.md:3:description: \\\"CLI to manage emails via IMAP/SMTP. Use `himalaya` to list, read, write, reply, forward, search, and organize emails from the terminal. Supports multiple accounts and message composition with MML (MIME Meta Language).\\\"\\n/app/skills/himalaya/SKILL.md:101:### Search Emails\\n/app/skills/notion/SKILL.md:45:**Search for pages and data sources:**\\n/app/skills/notion/SKILL.md:48:curl -X POST \\\"https://api.notion.com/v1/search\\\" \\\\\\n/app/skills/notion/SKILL.md:163:- **Search results:** Databases return as `\\\"object\\\": \\\"data_source\\\"` with their `data_source_id`\\n/app/skills/notion/SKILL.md:165:- **Finding the data_source_id:** Search for the database, or call `GET /v1/data_sources/{data_source_id}`\\n/app/skills/obsidian/SKILL.md:61:Search\\n/app/skills/obsidian/SKILL.md:63:- `obsidian-cli search \\\"query\\\"` (note names)\\n/app/skills/obsidian/SKILL.md:64:- `obsidian-cli search-content \\\"query\\\"` (inside notes; shows snippets + lines)\\n/app/skills/openai-image-gen/SKILL.md:47:python3 {baseDir}/scripts/gen.py --model gpt-image-1.5 --background transparent --output-format webp\\n/app/skills/openai-image-gen/SKILL.md:84:  - `--output-format`: `png` (default), `jpeg`, or `webp`\\n/app/skills/openai-image-gen/SKILL.md:90:- `*.png`, `*.jpeg`, or `*.webp` images (output format depends on model + `--output-format`)\\n/app/skills/openai-whisper/SKILL.md:4:homepage: https://openai.com/research/whisper\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:27:Oracle bundles your prompt + selected files into one “one-shot” request so another model can answer with real repo context (API or browser automation). Treat output as advisory: verify against code + tests.\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:29:## Main use case (browser, GPT‑5.2 Pro)\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:31:Default workflow here: `--engine browser` with GPT‑5.2 Pro in ChatGPT. This is the common “long think” path: ~10 minutes to ~1 hour is normal; expect a stored session you can reattach to.\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:35:- Engine: browser (`--engine browser`)\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:42:3. Use browser mode for the usual GPT‑5.2 Pro workflow; use API only when you explicitly want it.\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:58:- Browser run (main path; long-running is normal):\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:59:  - `oracle --engine browser --model gpt-5.2-pro -p \\\"<task>\\\" --file \\\"src/**\\\"`\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:84:## Engines (API vs browser)\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:86:- Auto-pick: `api` when `OPENAI_API_KEY` is set; otherwise `browser`.\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:87:- Browser supports GPT + Gemini only; use `--engine api` for Claude/Grok/Codex or multi-model runs.\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:88:- Browser attachments:\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:89:  - `--browser-attachments auto|never|always` (auto pastes inline up to ~60k chars then uploads).\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:90:- Remote browser host:\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:92:  - Client: `oracle --engine browser --remote-host <host:port> --remote-token <secret> -p \\\"<task>\\\" --file \\\"src/**\\\"`\\n/app/skills/oracle/SKILL.md:97:- Runs may detach or take a long time (browser + GPT‑5.2 Pro often does). If the CLI times out: don’t re-run; reattach.\\n/app/skills/ordercli/SKILL.md:60:- Browser login: `ordercli foodora login --email you@example.com --password-stdin --browser`\\n/app/skills/ordercli/SKILL.md:61:- Reuse profile: `--browser-profile \\\"$HOME/Library/Application Support/ordercli/browser-profile\\\"`\\n/app/skills/ordercli/SKILL.md:62:- Import Chrome cookies: `ordercli foodora cookies chrome --profile \\\"Default\\\"`\\n/app/skills/ordercli/SKILL.md:66:- `ordercli foodora session chrome --url https://www.foodora.at/ --profile \\\"Default\\\"`\\n/app/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md:3:description: Search and analyze your own session logs (older/parent conversations) using jq.\\n/app/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md:9:Search your complete conversation history stored in session JSONL files. Use this when a user references older/parent conversations or asks what was said before.\\n/app/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md:58:### Search for keyword in assistant responses\\n/app/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md:98:### Search across ALL sessions for a phrase\\n/app/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md:89:- **Best practice**: If files are large (>10k words), include grep search patterns in SKILL.md\\n/app/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md:251:Example: When designing a `frontend-webapp-builder` skill for queries like \\\"Build me a todo app\\\" or \\\"Build me a dashboard to track my steps,\\\" the analysis shows:\\n/app/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md:253:1. Writing a frontend webapp requires the same boilerplate HTML/React each time\\n/app/skills/sonoscli/SKILL.md:41:- Spotify search (via SMAPI): `sonos smapi search --service \\\"Spotify\\\" --category tracks \\\"query\\\"`\\n/app/skills/sonoscli/SKILL.md:46:- Spotify Web API search is optional and requires `SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID/SECRET`.\\n/app/skills/spotify-player/SKILL.md:3:description: Terminal Spotify playback/search via spogo (preferred) or spotify_player.\\n/app/skills/spotify-player/SKILL.md:35:Use `spogo` **(preferred)** for Spotify playback/search. Fall back to `spotify_player` if needed.\\n/app/skills/spotify-player/SKILL.md:44:- Import cookies: `spogo auth import --browser chrome`\\n/app/skills/spotify-player/SKILL.md:48:- Search: `spogo search track \\\"query\\\"`\\n/app/skills/spotify-player/SKILL.md:55:- Search: `spotify_player search \\\"query\\\"`\\n/app/skills/things-mac/SKILL.md:3:description: Manage Things 3 via the `things` CLI on macOS (add/update projects+todos via URL scheme; read/search/list from the local Things database). Use when a user asks OpenClaw to add a task to Things, list inbox/today/upcoming, search tasks, or inspect projects/areas/tags.\\n/app/skills/things-mac/SKILL.md:28:Use `things` to read your local Things database (inbox/today/search/projects/areas/tags) and to add/update todos via the Things URL scheme.\\n/app/skills/things-mac/SKILL.md:42:- `things search \\\"query\\\"`\\n/app/skills/things-mac/SKILL.md:68:- First: get the ID (UUID column): `things search \\\"milk\\\" --limit 5`\\n/app/skills/wacli/SKILL.md:3:description: Send WhatsApp messages to other people or search/sync WhatsApp history via the wacli CLI (not for normal user chats).\\n/app/skills/wacli/SKILL.md:34:Use `wacli` only when the user explicitly asks you to message someone else on WhatsApp or when they ask to sync/search WhatsApp history.\\n/app/skills/wacli/SKILL.md:53:- `wacli messages search \\\"query\\\" --limit 20 --chat <jid>`\\n/app/skills/wacli/SKILL.md:54:- `wacli messages search \\\"invoice\\\" --after 2025-01-01 --before 2025-12-31`\\n/app/skills/xurl/SKILL.md:3:description: A CLI tool for making authenticated requests to the X (Twitter) API. Use this skill when you need to post tweets, reply, quote, search, read posts, manage followers, send DMs, upload media, or interact with any X API v2 endpoint.\\n/app/skills/xurl/SKILL.md:118:| Search posts              | `xurl search \\\"QUERY\\\" -n 10`                           |\\n/app/skills/xurl/SKILL.md:195:# Search recent posts (default 10 results)\\n/app/skills/